{"type":"message","id":"e96196b9","parentId":"d0ca15cd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:59:42.178Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qouks68q7ys3_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4949\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=1824\n[file inferred from ACTION] an\n[mutation proposed] an\n[master 4bb0065] pulse: 2026-03-24 155915\n 6 files changed, 252 insertions(+), 96 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 155915.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 155915.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 155815.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 155915 - The Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment is the clear next step - the formula `score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)` was identified as the key to distinguishing constant-format tokens from research trajectory tokens. I need to implement and test this.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"cool-ember","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4949\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=1824\n[file inferred from ACTION] an\n[mutation proposed] an\n[master 4bb0065] pulse: 2026-03-24 155915\n 6 files changed, 252 insertions(+), 96 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 155915.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 155915.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 155815.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 155915 - The Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment is the clear next step - the formula `score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)` was identified as the key to distinguishing constant-format tokens from research trajectory tokens. I need to implement and test this.\n","name":"powershell Bypass"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382382176}}
{"type":"message","id":"1dcef2aa","parentId":"e96196b9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:59:42.180Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qouks68q7ys3_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 155815\n\n## Applied Mutations\nJust applied: research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md (appended)\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n2. Just completed CFI Compression Experiment with key findings\r\n3. Next pending action: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n4. Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n5. Need to test if this distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n\r\nThe most logical next step is to run the hybrid scoring experiment. The synthesis document `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` outlines the three strategies (A, B, C), and Strategy C is the hybrid approach.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Create an experiment file for the hybrid scoring approach\r\n2. Design the experiment properly to test if score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) works\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action advances the goals:\r\n- The pending experiment is clearly the next step\r\n- I need to document the experiment design so it can be run\r\n- I should create a file that outlines the experiment methodology\r\n\r\nThis is a documentation/planning action that sets up the experiment execution.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified Strategy C (hybrid CFI×Freq scoring) as the next experiment, but only the 80/20 split test was run. The hybrid scoring formula needs its own evaluation against the binary threshold results.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a detailed experiment plan for Strategy C (hybrid CFI×Freq scoring) that can be executed on the pulse corpus, establishing the test methodology before running.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n## Experiment Plan\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** PLANNED\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\r\n- **DEPRESS** constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1.00 → score ≈ 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0)\r\n  - Wait: this actually gives same score. Need to reconsider.\r\n- **ELEVATE** research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5 → score < CFI)\r\n- The min(1, freq/120) term penalizes high-frequency tokens\r\n\r\n**Revised Formula Analysis:**\r\n- \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00): score = 1.0 × min(1, 160/120) = 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0\r\n- \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96): score = 0.96 × min(1, 136/120) = 0.96 × 1.0 = 0.96\r\n- \"temporal\" (freq=40, CFI=0.70): score = 0.70 × min(1, 40/120) = 0.70 × 0.33 = 0.23\r\n\r\n**Problem:** The min(1, x) saturates at freq=120. Need different penalty function.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Revised Scoring Function\r\n**score(T) = CFI(T) × freq_penalty(T)**\r\n\r\nWhere:\r\n```\r\nfreq_penalty(T) = {\r\n    0.0                    if freq(T) < 3      (noise)\r\n    freq(T) / 120          if 3 ≤ freq(T) < 120  (normal range)\r\n    1.0                    if freq(T) ≥ 120     (capped)\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\n- Constant format (freq=160, CFI=1.00): score = 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 ← Still wrong!\r\n- Need INVERSE penalty for high frequency\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Final Scoring Function\r\n**score(T) = CFI(T) × log(1 + freq(T)) / log(121)**\r\n\r\nThis normalizes frequency to [0, 1] log scale:\r\n- freq=1: score = CFI × log(2)/log(121) ≈ CFI × 0.09\r\n- freq=120: score = CFI × log(121)/log(121) = CFI × 1.0\r\n- freq=160: score = CFI × log(161)/log(121) ≈ CFI × 1.11 (clamped to 1.0)\r\n\r\n**Still problematic for constant tokens.**\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Alternative: Binary Frequency Cap\r\n**score(T) = CFI(T) if freq(T) < 120 ELSE CFI(T) × 0.1**\r\n\r\nThis penalizes tokens appearing in 75%+ of pulses by 10×.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Test Corpus\r\n- 200 pulses (same as Strategy A/B)\r\n- Token corpus: all unique tokens from pulses\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n1. **Precision@K**: Among top-K tokens, what fraction are \"research trajectory\" vs \"constant format\"?\r\n2. **Recall@K**: Do we capture the actual research tokens?\r\n3. **F1 Score**: Balance precision vs recall\r\n\r\n### Baseline Comparison\r\n- Strategy A (CFI ≥ 0.7): precision=0.5653, recall=0.071\r\n- Strategy B (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)): Expected improvement\r\n\r\n### Execution\r\n```powershell\r\n# For each token T:\r\n$logFreqFactor = [Math]::Log(1 + $freq) / [Math]::Log(121)\r\n$score = $CFI * $logFreqFactor\r\nif ($\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:58:41\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382382178}}
