{"type":"message","id":"7f7c526e","parentId":"7bdb7a30","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:59:50.439Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0kncaf7knd3e_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 155915\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. The main pending action is the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n3. Key insight: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n4. The CFI Compression Synthesis document has been created with findings\r\n\r\nThe pending experiment needs to be run. Looking at the notes, I need to:\r\n- Test if this scoring formula distinguishes \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\n- Run 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nBut wait - I'm a stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction. The previous pulse noted \"No mutations applied this cycle.\"\r\n\r\nThe key pending action is the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment. I should take concrete action to advance this. Let me think about what concrete file edit would help:\r\n\r\n1. I could create a script to run the experiment\r\n2. I could update the experiment design document\r\n3. I could implement the scoring function to test it\r\n\r\nGiven the goal is to advance the Hybrid CFI×Freq experiment, the most concrete action would be to either:\r\n- Create the experiment runner script\r\n- Update the research document with the refined hypothesis and test plan\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete experiment runner that tests this hypothesis. I'll create a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Loads pulse data\r\n2. Applies the hybrid scoring formula\r\n3. Compares against binary thresholds\r\n4. Outputs results\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete, specific action that advances the pending goal.\r\n\r\nLet me draft the mutation:\r\n\r\nSince this is a new file, I'll use \"(new file)\" for old_text.\r\n\r\nActually, I need to think about what the most impactful single action is. The experiment requires:\r\n1. Data collection (200 pulses)\r\n\r\n\r\n2. Applying the formula\r\n3. Comparing results\r\n\r\nI'll develop a targeted script that tests the hybrid scoring approach systematically. The script will generate synthetic data to simulate pulse characteristics, then apply the CFI×Freq formula with precise threshold logic. This allows me to validate the scoring mechanism's effectiveness in distinguishing constant versus trajectory-based frequency patterns.\r\n\r\nThe core logic involves calculating a hybrid score using the formula, then evaluating its classification performance against predefined threshold boundaries. By running multiple iterations, I can gather statistically meaningful insights about the scoring strategy's precision and recall.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment is the clear next step - the formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` was identified as the key to distinguishing constant-format tokens from research trajectory tokens. I need to implement and test this.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate an experiment runner script that implements the hybrid scoring formula and compares it against binary threshold approaches, generating synthetic pulse data to validate the hypothesis before running on real data.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n# Tests: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# Hypothesis: This distinguishes constant-format (freq≈160, CFI=1) from research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\n\r\n$results = @()\r\n\r\n# Generate synthetic pulse data reflecting known distributions\r\n# Constants: freq=160, CFI=1.00 (metaprogramming artifacts)\r\n# Trajectory: freq in [10-120], CFI in [0.5-0.96] (true research)\r\n# Noise: freq<10 or CFI<0.5 (random)\r\n\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt 200; $i++) {\r\n    $token = \"token_$i\"\r\n    $is_constant = $i -lt 80  # 40% constants\r\n    \r\n    if ($is_constant) {\r\n        $freq = 160\r\n        $cfi = 1.00\r\n        $label = $true  # Should be selected\r\n    } else {\r\n        $freq = Get-Random -Minimum 5 -Maximum 130\r\n        $cfi = Get-Random -Minimum 0.3 -Maximum 0.96\r\n        $label = ($freq -ge 10 -and $cfi -ge 0.5)  # Ground truth\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $hybrid_score = $cfi * [Math]::Min(1, $freq / 120)\r\n    $binary_selected = ($cfi -ge 0.5 -and $freq -ge 3 -and $freq -lt 120)\r\n    \r\n    $results += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        Token = $token\r\n        Freq = $freq\r\n        CFI = $cfi\r\n        Label = $label\r\n        HybridScore = $hybrid_score\r\n        HybridSelected = ($hybrid_score -gt 0.5)\r\n        BinarySelected = $binary_selected\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Analyze results\r\n$true_positives_hybrid = ($results | Where-Object { $_.HybridSelected -and $_.Label }).Count\r\n$false_positives_hybrid = ($results | Where-Object { $_.HybridSelected -and -not $_.Label }).Count\r\n$true_negatives_hybrid = ($results | Where-Object { -not $_.HybridSelected -and -not $_.Label }).Count\r\n$false_negatives_hybrid = ($results | Where-Object { -not $_.HybridSelected -and $_.Label }).Count\r\n\r\n$recall_hybrid = $true_positives_hybrid / ($true_positives_hybrid + $false_negatives_hybrid)\r\n$precision_hybrid = $true_positives_hybrid / ($true_positives\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:59:41\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382390437}}
